it struck him that in moments of crisis one is never fighting against an external enemy but always against ones own body on the battlefield in the torture chamber on a sinking ship the issues that you are fighting for are always forgotten because the body swells up until it fills the universe and even when you are not paralyzed by fright or screaming in pain life is a moment to moment struggle against hunger or cold or sleeplessness against a sour stomachg or an aching tooth